examples: This is a turbo tournament: the blinds increase every 5 minutes! Level 1 = 150/300; level 2 = 200/400; etc.

definitions.definition: Causing or relating to increased speed .
Very, super, etc.; usually relating to a qualitative value (as opposed to quantitative).
examples: They act turbo wasted when they have more than a few beers in them.

main_definition: ( said of a poker tournament ) With rapidly -increasing blind levels.
secondary_definitions: ( computing , video games ) Causing or relating to increased speed .
( informal , nonstandard ) Very, super, etc.; usually relating to a qualitative value (as opposed to quantitative).
